<paragraph id="8BFE36BBFFF8FFBB02CFC2E7BFDBFCA5" blockId="2.[151,1129,219,1108]" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB02CFC2E7BC52FD25" bold="true" box="[151,262,732,756]" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B4AFFF8FFBB0357C2E7BCE4FD25" author="BRAVO F." box="[271,432,732,756]" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" pagination="31 - 37" refId="ref5118" refString="BRAVO F. 2001 c: Trichomyia quatei (Diptera, Psychodidae), uma nova especie do nordeste brasileiro. Acta Biologica Leopoldensia 23 (1): 31 - 37." type="journal article" year="2001">BRAVO (2001c)</bibRefCitation>
proposed an unnamed group of three Neotropical species with gonocoxites with long posterior arms and long bristles on their inner margins including 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB060BC2C6BDB0FCE5" authorityName="Barretto" authorityYear="1954" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB060BC2C6BDB0FCE5" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">T. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB02AAC326BCDAFCE5" box="[242,398,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB02AAC326BCDFFCE5" authorityName="Satchell" authorityYear="1956" box="[242,395,797,820]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">T. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB039BC326BF75FCE5" authorityName="Bravo" authorityYear="2001" box="[451,545,797,820]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quatei">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB039BC326BF75FCE5" box="[451,545,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">T. quatei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B4AFFF8FFBB0076C327BE7EFCE5" author="BEJARANO E. E. &amp; PEREZ-DORIA A. &amp; SIERRA D." box="[558,810,796,820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" pagination="295 - 300" refId="ref4781" refString="BEJARANO E. E., PEREZ-DORIA A. &amp; SIERRA D. 2009 a: Descripcion de una nueva especie de Trichomyia (Diptera: Psychodidae) de los Andes Colombianos. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 68 (3 - 4): 295 - 300." type="journal article" year="2009">BEJARANO et al. (2009a)</bibRefCitation>
added 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB0120C326B94AFCE5" authorityName="Bejarano, Perez-Doria &amp; Sierra" authorityYear="2009" box="[888,1054,797,820]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="risaraldensis">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB0120C326B94AFCE5" box="[888,1054,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">T. risaraldensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB060BC326BC62FC85" authorityName="Quate" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudodactylis">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB060BC326BC62FC85" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">T. pseudodactylis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to this unnamed group. This taxon is here assigned the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB0190C306BD9FFCA5" authority="Bravo &amp; Araújo &amp; Uefs, 2013" authorityName="Bravo &amp; Araújo &amp; Uefs" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Brachiotrichomyia">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB0190C306BD9FFCA5" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">Brachiotrichomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20657D2FFF8FFBB028AC367BC0CFCA2" box="[210,344,860,884]" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and classified as a subgenus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE36BBFFF8FFBB02EDC346BE85FB85" blockId="2.[151,1129,219,1108]" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB02EDC346BC2CFC45" authority="Bravo &amp; Araújo &amp; Uefs, 2013" authorityName="Bravo &amp; Araújo &amp; Uefs" authorityYear="2013" box="[181,376,893,916]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Brachiotrichomyia">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB02EDC346BC2CFC45" box="[181,376,893,916]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">Brachiotrichomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20657D2FFF8FFBB0325C347BCAAFC42" box="[381,510,892,916]" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" rank="subGenus">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a natural group with at least one exclusive character: ovoid aedeagal complex, fused apically. Two diagnostic characters of the new subgenus show variations: the first character refers to the presence of sensilla in depressed pits on palpal segments 1 and 2 that are observed in all species (except 
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB0037C3E6BE7EFC25" box="[623,810,989,1012]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB0037C3E6BE73FC25" authorityName="Quate" authorityYear="1996" box="[623,807,989,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudodactylis">T. pseudodactylis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
with sensilla only on segment 2, which is assumed to be a secondary modification in that species); the second character refers to the presence of an elongated, unsclerotized gonostylus, although this structure would be secondarily absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB0321C406BC8AFB85" authorityName="Barretto" authorityYear="1954" box="[377,478,1085,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB0321C406BC8AFB85" box="[377,478,1085,1108]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">T. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D38FFF8FFBB0048C406BFF6FB85" authorityName="Satchell" authorityYear="1956" box="[528,674,1085,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B935EAA9FFF8FFBB0048C406BFF6FB85" box="[528,674,1085,1108]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="331">T. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B4AFFF8FFBB0168C407BE9AFB85" author="BRAVO F." box="[816,974,1084,1108]" pageId="2" pageNumber="331" pagination="31 - 37" refId="ref5118" refString="BRAVO F. 2001 c: Trichomyia quatei (Diptera, Psychodidae), uma nova especie do nordeste brasileiro. Acta Biologica Leopoldensia 23 (1): 31 - 37." type="journal article" year="2001">BRAVO (2001c)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
